postcontent: I SOMETIMES DO NO RECEIVE EMAIL SENT VIA ARMSLIST,PLEASE EMAIL ME DIRECTLY VIA :     REDACTEDHere's a super nice, unfired, Pre-Ban Chinese Norinco Type 56-S...the semi-auto version of the Chinese military AK. Chambered for the 7.62x39mm, this rifle has a 16-1/4" chrome lined barrel with threaded muzzle brake and bayonet lug. The Chinese AK's are highly respected and are among the best available but thanks to the Clinton era import ban, they have been getting harder and harder to come by. The thicker 1.5mm stamped receivers are more durable than many of the 1mm thick Eastern block rifles, and the Chinese guns really are built to last. This rifle is in excellent original condition and I'd grade it about 99% overall. There is no rust or pitting. The stocks are in excellent condition with just a few tiny handling marks (these rifles seemed to ship new with a few handling marks). This rifle was a relatively early Sile import and has a blued bolt and the /66\ arsenal marking on the left side of the trunnion.
